{"video_id": "bDU3necB7wM", "title": "Daily Evening Bhagavatam Discourse | HH Stoka Krishna Swami | SB 1.13.8 | 24-09-2022", "speaker": "HH Stoka Krishna Swami", "youtube_url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bDU3necB7wM", "duration": 863, "segments": [{"start": 0.0, "end": 3.68, "text": " Om Agyana Timiraandasya Gyananjanishalakaya"}, {"start": 3.68, "end": 7.78, "text": " Chaksharunmeelitam Yena Tasmai Shri Gurave Namaha"}, {"start": 7.78, "end": 11.32, "text": " Namah Om Vishnupadaya Krishna Preshtaya Bhutale"}, {"start": 11.32, "end": 14.74, "text": " Srimate Bhaktivedanta Swamin Nithinamine"}, {"start": 14.74, "end": 18.82, "text": " Namaste Saraswate Deve Gauravani Pracharine"}, {"start": 18.82, "end": 22.46, "text": " Nirvishesha Shunyavadi Pashchatyade Shatarine"}, {"start": 22.46, "end": 25.96, "text": " Jaya Shri Krishna Chaitanya Prabhu Nityananda"}, {"start": 25.96, "end": 29.92, "text": " Shri Advaita Gadadhara Sri Vasadi Gauravakta Vrinda"}, {"start": 29.92, "end": 33.78, "text": " Hare Krishna Hare Krishna Krishna Krishna Hare Hare"}, {"start": 33.78, "end": 37.1, "text": " Hare Rama Hare Rama Rama Rama Hare Hare"}, {"start": 37.1, "end": 41.32, "text": " Om Namo Bhagavate Vasudevaya Narayanam Namaskritya"}, {"start": 41.32, "end": 46.480000000000004, "text": " Naram Jai Vanarottamam Devi Saraswati Vyasam Tato Jayam Udi Rayet"}, {"start": 46.480000000000004, "end": 52.68000000000001, "text": " In this session we will be discussing from the 8th verse of the 13th chapter of the 1st canto of Sriman Bhagavatam."}, {"start": 52.68000000000001, "end": 57.64, "text": " Yudhishthira Uvacha Api Smaratha No Yushmat"}, {"start": 57.64, "end": 61.58, "text": " Paksha Chhaya Same Dhitam"}, {"start": 61.58, "end": 65.3, "text": " Vipad Gannat Vishag Nyader"}, {"start": 65.3, "end": 74.2, "text": " Mochitayat Samatra Kaha"}, {"start": 74.2, "end": 77.58, "text": " The meaning of this verse is"}, {"start": 77.58, "end": 79.42, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira said"}, {"start": 79.42, "end": 80.74000000000001, "text": " My uncle"}, {"start": 80.74000000000001, "end": 82.88, "text": " He is addressing Vidura"}, {"start": 82.88, "end": 84.76, "text": " Yudhishthira is addressing Vidura"}, {"start": 84.76, "end": 85.62, "text": " My uncle"}, {"start": 85.62, "end": 87.62, "text": " Do you remember how you always"}, {"start": 87.64, "end": 92.08, "text": " protected us along with our mother from all sorts of calamities"}, {"start": 92.08, "end": 99.48, "text": " Your partiality like the wings of a bird saved us from poisoning and arson"}, {"start": 99.48, "end": 103.0, "text": " Now Srila Prabhupada explains this"}, {"start": 103.0, "end": 106.0, "text": " What is this poisoning and arson"}, {"start": 106.0, "end": 109.2, "text": " In the purport Srila Prabhupada says"}, {"start": 109.2, "end": 112.5, "text": " Due to Pandu's death at an early age"}, {"start": 112.5, "end": 116.76, "text": " His minor children and widow were the object of special care"}, {"start": 116.76, "end": 117.62, "text": " By the elderly men"}, {"start": 117.62, "end": 119.62, "text": " The family members of the family"}, {"start": 119.62, "end": 121.62, "text": " Especially Bhishma Deva"}, {"start": 121.62, "end": 123.62, "text": " And Mahatma Vidura"}, {"start": 123.62, "end": 127.62, "text": " Vidura is addressed as Mahatma"}, {"start": 127.62, "end": 129.62, "text": " Because"}, {"start": 129.62, "end": 131.62, "text": " He was not only"}, {"start": 131.62, "end": 133.62, "text": " Very"}, {"start": 133.62, "end": 135.62, "text": " Conscious of his responsibility"}, {"start": 135.62, "end": 137.62, "text": " As an elderly member of the family"}, {"start": 137.62, "end": 139.62, "text": " But he was also"}, {"start": 139.62, "end": 141.62, "text": " Spiritually"}, {"start": 141.62, "end": 143.62, "text": " Self realized"}, {"start": 143.62, "end": 145.62, "text": " Spiritually advanced"}, {"start": 145.62, "end": 147.62, "text": " And self realized"}, {"start": 147.62, "end": 149.62, "text": " After him"}, {"start": 149.62, "end": 151.62, "text": " His travelling"}, {"start": 151.62, "end": 153.62, "text": " To pace the pilgrimage"}, {"start": 153.62, "end": 155.62, "text": " And inquiring from Maitreya Rishi"}, {"start": 155.62, "end": 159.62, "text": " And becoming spiritually enlightened"}, {"start": 159.62, "end": 163.62, "text": " So therefore he is addressed as Mahatma Vidura"}, {"start": 163.62, "end": 165.62, "text": " This Mahatma title"}, {"start": 165.62, "end": 167.62, "text": " Is"}, {"start": 167.62, "end": 169.62, "text": " Not for simply somebody"}, {"start": 169.62, "end": 171.62, "text": " Great by some material estimation"}, {"start": 171.62, "end": 173.62, "text": " No"}, {"start": 173.62, "end": 175.62, "text": " It is reserved for"}, {"start": 175.62, "end": 177.62, "text": " Great devotees"}, {"start": 177.62, "end": 179.62, "text": " According to the Bhagavad Gita"}, {"start": 179.62, "end": 181.62, "text": " Mahatma anastumam partha"}, {"start": 181.62, "end": 183.62, "text": " Daiveem prakritim ashritah"}, {"start": 183.62, "end": 185.62, "text": " Bhajanti ananya manaso"}, {"start": 185.62, "end": 189.62, "text": " Gyaatva bhutadim abhyayam"}, {"start": 189.62, "end": 191.62, "text": " According to the Bhagavad Gita"}, {"start": 191.62, "end": 193.62, "text": " Who is to be called a Mahatma"}, {"start": 193.62, "end": 195.62, "text": " One who has taken shelter of Krishna's"}, {"start": 195.62, "end": 197.62, "text": " Internal spiritual potency"}, {"start": 197.62, "end": 199.62, "text": " And"}, {"start": 199.62, "end": 201.62, "text": " The symptom of having taken"}, {"start": 201.62, "end": 203.62, "text": " Shelter of Krishna's internal potency"}, {"start": 203.62, "end": 205.62, "text": " Is that"}, {"start": 205.62, "end": 207.62, "text": " Such a person"}, {"start": 207.62, "end": 209.62, "text": " Is always engaged in"}, {"start": 209.62, "end": 211.62, "text": " Pure devotional service to Krishna"}, {"start": 211.62, "end": 213.62, "text": " Without any interruption"}, {"start": 215.62, "end": 217.62, "text": " So Vidura was"}, {"start": 217.62, "end": 219.62, "text": " Such a pure devotee"}, {"start": 219.62, "end": 221.62, "text": " Of Krishna"}, {"start": 221.62, "end": 223.62, "text": " Therefore he is addressed as"}, {"start": 223.62, "end": 225.62, "text": " Mahatma Vidura"}, {"start": 225.62, "end": 227.62, "text": " Vidura was more or less"}, {"start": 227.62, "end": 229.62, "text": " Partial to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 229.62, "end": 231.62, "text": " Due to their political position"}, {"start": 231.62, "end": 233.62, "text": " The Pandavas"}, {"start": 233.62, "end": 235.62, "text": " Were fatherless"}, {"start": 235.62, "end": 237.62, "text": " Kunti was staying"}, {"start": 237.62, "end": 239.62, "text": " With her minor sons"}, {"start": 239.62, "end": 241.62, "text": " In the palace of"}, {"start": 241.62, "end": 243.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 243.62, "end": 245.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra was the Ketakar king"}, {"start": 245.62, "end": 247.62, "text": " But Dhritarashtra was"}, {"start": 247.62, "end": 249.62, "text": " Not treating the Pandavas"}, {"start": 249.62, "end": 251.62, "text": " Equally with his own sons"}, {"start": 251.62, "end": 253.62, "text": " Because Dhritarashtra had"}, {"start": 253.62, "end": 255.62, "text": " A"}, {"start": 255.62, "end": 257.62, "text": " Inner desire"}, {"start": 257.62, "end": 259.62, "text": " That somehow"}, {"start": 259.62, "end": 261.62, "text": " His own sons"}, {"start": 261.62, "end": 263.62, "text": " Should become the"}, {"start": 263.62, "end": 265.62, "text": " Emperors"}, {"start": 265.62, "end": 267.62, "text": " Of the world"}, {"start": 267.62, "end": 269.62, "text": " And not the"}, {"start": 269.62, "end": 271.62, "text": " Sons of Pandu"}, {"start": 271.62, "end": 273.62, "text": " Who are the"}, {"start": 273.62, "end": 275.62, "text": " Rightful claimants"}, {"start": 275.62, "end": 277.62, "text": " To the throne"}, {"start": 277.62, "end": 279.62, "text": " Of Hastinapura"}, {"start": 279.62, "end": 281.62, "text": " So"}, {"start": 281.62, "end": 283.62, "text": " Duryodhana plotted"}, {"start": 283.62, "end": 285.62, "text": " To"}, {"start": 285.62, "end": 287.62, "text": " Actually"}, {"start": 287.62, "end": 289.62, "text": " Kill the Pandavas"}, {"start": 289.62, "end": 291.62, "text": " Before they could"}, {"start": 291.62, "end": 293.62, "text": " Actually become adults"}, {"start": 293.62, "end": 295.62, "text": " And"}, {"start": 295.62, "end": 297.62, "text": " Supported his"}, {"start": 297.62, "end": 299.62, "text": " Son"}, {"start": 299.62, "end": 301.62, "text": " Duryodhana"}, {"start": 301.62, "end": 303.62, "text": " In all his nefarious"}, {"start": 303.62, "end": 305.62, "text": " Activities"}, {"start": 305.62, "end": 307.62, "text": " So"}, {"start": 307.62, "end": 309.62, "text": " Srila Prabhupada explains"}, {"start": 309.62, "end": 311.62, "text": " Although Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 311.62, "end": 313.62, "text": " Was equally careful for the minor children"}, {"start": 313.62, "end": 315.62, "text": " Of Maharaja Pandu"}, {"start": 315.62, "end": 317.62, "text": " He was one of the intriguing"}, {"start": 317.62, "end": 319.62, "text": " Parties who wanted to wash"}, {"start": 319.62, "end": 321.62, "text": " Away the descendants of Pandu"}, {"start": 321.62, "end": 323.62, "text": " And replace them by raising"}, {"start": 323.62, "end": 325.62, "text": " His own sons to become"}, {"start": 325.62, "end": 327.62, "text": " Rulers of the kingdom"}, {"start": 327.62, "end": 329.62, "text": " Mahatma Vidura could"}, {"start": 329.62, "end": 331.62, "text": " Follow this intrigue"}, {"start": 331.62, "end": 333.62, "text": " Of Dhritarashtra and company"}, {"start": 333.62, "end": 335.62, "text": " And therefore"}, {"start": 335.62, "end": 337.62, "text": " Even though he was a faithful servitor"}, {"start": 337.62, "end": 339.62, "text": " Of his eldest brother Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 339.62, "end": 341.62, "text": " He did not like"}, {"start": 341.62, "end": 343.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra's political"}, {"start": 343.62, "end": 345.62, "text": " Ambition for the sake of his own"}, {"start": 345.62, "end": 347.62, "text": " Sons"}, {"start": 347.62, "end": 349.62, "text": " Therefore Vidura was"}, {"start": 349.62, "end": 351.62, "text": " Very careful about"}, {"start": 351.62, "end": 353.62, "text": " The protection of the Pandavas"}, {"start": 353.62, "end": 355.62, "text": " And their widow mother"}, {"start": 355.62, "end": 357.62, "text": " Kunti"}, {"start": 357.62, "end": 359.62, "text": " Thus he was so to speak"}, {"start": 359.62, "end": 361.62, "text": " Partial to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 361.62, "end": 363.62, "text": " Preferring them to the sons of"}, {"start": 363.62, "end": 365.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra although"}, {"start": 365.62, "end": 367.62, "text": " Both of them were equally affectionate"}, {"start": 367.62, "end": 369.62, "text": " In his ordinary eyes"}, {"start": 371.62, "end": 373.62, "text": " See how Vidura is carefully"}, {"start": 375.62, "end": 377.62, "text": " On the one hand"}, {"start": 377.62, "end": 379.62, "text": " Trying to protect the Pandavas"}, {"start": 379.62, "end": 381.62, "text": " On the other hand"}, {"start": 381.62, "end": 383.62, "text": " He is also"}, {"start": 383.62, "end": 385.62, "text": " Showing equal affection to"}, {"start": 385.62, "end": 387.62, "text": " The Pandavas and Kauravas"}, {"start": 387.62, "end": 389.62, "text": " Because both of them are"}, {"start": 389.62, "end": 391.62, "text": " Sons of his"}, {"start": 391.62, "end": 393.62, "text": " Two brothers"}, {"start": 395.62, "end": 397.62, "text": " He was equally"}, {"start": 397.62, "end": 399.62, "text": " Affectionate to both the camps of"}, {"start": 399.62, "end": 401.62, "text": " Nebus in the sense that"}, {"start": 401.62, "end": 403.62, "text": " He always chastised"}, {"start": 403.62, "end": 405.62, "text": " Duryodhana for his"}, {"start": 405.62, "end": 407.62, "text": " Intriguing policy against"}, {"start": 407.62, "end": 409.62, "text": " His cousins"}, {"start": 409.62, "end": 411.62, "text": " He always criticized his elder brother"}, {"start": 411.62, "end": 413.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra for his policy"}, {"start": 413.62, "end": 415.62, "text": " Of encouragement to his sons"}, {"start": 415.62, "end": 417.62, "text": " At the same time"}, {"start": 417.62, "end": 419.62, "text": " He was always alert in giving"}, {"start": 419.62, "end": 421.62, "text": " Special protection to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 421.62, "end": 423.62, "text": " All these different"}, {"start": 423.62, "end": 425.62, "text": " Activities of Vidura"}, {"start": 425.62, "end": 427.62, "text": " Within the palace politics"}, {"start": 427.62, "end": 429.62, "text": " Made him well known"}, {"start": 429.62, "end": 431.62, "text": " As partial to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 431.62, "end": 433.62, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 433.62, "end": 435.62, "text": " Has referred to the"}, {"start": 435.62, "end": 437.62, "text": " Past history of Vidura"}, {"start": 437.62, "end": 439.62, "text": " Before his going away from home"}, {"start": 439.62, "end": 441.62, "text": " For a prolonged pilgrim's journey"}, {"start": 441.62, "end": 443.62, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira reminded"}, {"start": 443.62, "end": 445.62, "text": " Vidura that"}, {"start": 445.62, "end": 447.62, "text": " He was equally kind and partial"}, {"start": 447.62, "end": 449.62, "text": " To his grown up nephews"}, {"start": 449.62, "end": 451.62, "text": " Even after the battle of Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 451.62, "end": 453.62, "text": " A great family disaster"}, {"start": 457.62, "end": 459.62, "text": " So Srila Prabhupada explains"}, {"start": 459.62, "end": 461.62, "text": " Before the battle of Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 461.62, "end": 463.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra's"}, {"start": 463.62, "end": 465.62, "text": " Policy was"}, {"start": 465.62, "end": 467.62, "text": " Peaceful annihilation of his nephews"}, {"start": 467.62, "end": 469.62, "text": " Peaceful annihilation"}, {"start": 469.62, "end": 471.62, "text": " Means they should be eliminated"}, {"start": 471.62, "end": 473.62, "text": " In such a way that"}, {"start": 473.62, "end": 475.62, "text": " Nobody will suspect any foul"}, {"start": 475.62, "end": 477.62, "text": " Play"}, {"start": 477.62, "end": 479.62, "text": " It should seem like"}, {"start": 479.62, "end": 481.62, "text": " They died"}, {"start": 481.62, "end": 483.62, "text": " Somehow"}, {"start": 483.62, "end": 485.62, "text": " And then because nobody is there"}, {"start": 485.62, "end": 487.62, "text": " To ascend the throne"}, {"start": 487.62, "end": 489.62, "text": " As descendants of Pandu"}, {"start": 489.62, "end": 491.62, "text": " Therefore"}, {"start": 491.62, "end": 493.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra's sons will become"}, {"start": 493.62, "end": 495.62, "text": " The claimants to the throne"}, {"start": 495.62, "end": 497.62, "text": " Of Hastinapura"}, {"start": 497.62, "end": 499.62, "text": " So this was"}, {"start": 499.62, "end": 501.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra's policy and plan"}, {"start": 501.62, "end": 503.62, "text": " And what did he do"}, {"start": 503.62, "end": 505.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra do?"}, {"start": 505.62, "end": 507.62, "text": " He ordered Purochana"}, {"start": 507.62, "end": 509.62, "text": " To build a house at"}, {"start": 509.62, "end": 511.62, "text": " Varanavata"}, {"start": 511.62, "end": 513.62, "text": " And when the building was finished"}, {"start": 513.62, "end": 515.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra desired"}, {"start": 515.62, "end": 517.62, "text": " That his brother's"}, {"start": 517.62, "end": 519.62, "text": " Family live there"}, {"start": 519.62, "end": 521.62, "text": " For some time"}, {"start": 521.62, "end": 523.62, "text": " Because the Pandavas and Kauravas"}, {"start": 523.62, "end": 525.62, "text": " Were sharing that palace"}, {"start": 525.62, "end": 527.62, "text": " In Hastinapura"}, {"start": 527.62, "end": 529.62, "text": " So Dhritarashtra said"}, {"start": 529.62, "end": 531.62, "text": " To the Pandavas"}, {"start": 531.62, "end": 533.62, "text": " You can go and live there comfortably"}, {"start": 533.62, "end": 535.62, "text": " This palace is for you"}, {"start": 535.62, "end": 537.62, "text": " Separately you can live"}, {"start": 537.62, "end": 539.62, "text": " When the Pandavas"}, {"start": 539.62, "end": 541.62, "text": " Were going there in the presence"}, {"start": 541.62, "end": 543.62, "text": " Of all the members of the royal family"}, {"start": 543.62, "end": 545.62, "text": " Vidura tactfully gave"}, {"start": 545.62, "end": 547.62, "text": " Instructions to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 547.62, "end": 549.62, "text": " About the future plan of Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 549.62, "end": 551.62, "text": " The Pandavas did not know"}, {"start": 551.62, "end": 553.62, "text": " What was Dhritarashtra's plan"}, {"start": 553.62, "end": 555.62, "text": " But Vidura knew"}, {"start": 555.62, "end": 557.62, "text": " And Vidura gave"}, {"start": 557.62, "end": 559.62, "text": " Instructions"}, {"start": 559.62, "end": 561.62, "text": " To Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 561.62, "end": 563.62, "text": " Very very tactfully"}, {"start": 563.62, "end": 565.62, "text": " About Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 565.62, "end": 567.62, "text": " Coming to know about it"}, {"start": 567.62, "end": 569.62, "text": " So this is specifically"}, {"start": 569.62, "end": 571.62, "text": " Described in the Mahabharata"}, {"start": 571.62, "end": 573.62, "text": " Adiparva 114"}, {"start": 573.62, "end": 575.62, "text": " He indirectly hinted"}, {"start": 575.62, "end": 577.62, "text": " What did he say"}, {"start": 577.62, "end": 579.62, "text": " What did Vidura say"}, {"start": 579.62, "end": 581.62, "text": " To Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 581.62, "end": 583.62, "text": " A weapon not made of steel"}, {"start": 583.62, "end": 585.62, "text": " Or any other material element"}, {"start": 585.62, "end": 587.62, "text": " Can be more sharp to kill an enemy"}, {"start": 587.62, "end": 589.62, "text": " And he who knows this"}, {"start": 589.62, "end": 591.62, "text": " Is never killed"}, {"start": 591.62, "end": 593.62, "text": " See"}, {"start": 593.62, "end": 595.62, "text": " In the form of a riddle"}, {"start": 595.62, "end": 597.62, "text": " He is telling something to Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 597.62, "end": 599.62, "text": " That is to say"}, {"start": 599.62, "end": 601.62, "text": " Vidura hinted"}, {"start": 601.62, "end": 603.62, "text": " That the party of the Pandavas"}, {"start": 603.62, "end": 605.62, "text": " Was being sent to Varanavata"}, {"start": 605.62, "end": 607.62, "text": " To be killed"}, {"start": 607.62, "end": 609.62, "text": " And thus"}, {"start": 609.62, "end": 611.62, "text": " He warned Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 611.62, "end": 613.62, "text": " To be very careful"}, {"start": 613.62, "end": 615.62, "text": " In their new residential palace"}, {"start": 615.62, "end": 617.62, "text": " He also gave"}, {"start": 617.62, "end": 619.62, "text": " Indications of fire"}, {"start": 619.62, "end": 621.62, "text": " And said that fire cannot extinguish the soul"}, {"start": 621.62, "end": 623.62, "text": " But can annihilate"}, {"start": 623.62, "end": 625.62, "text": " The material body"}, {"start": 625.62, "end": 627.62, "text": " But one who protects"}, {"start": 627.62, "end": 629.62, "text": " The soul can live"}, {"start": 629.62, "end": 631.62, "text": " Kunti could not follow such"}, {"start": 631.62, "end": 633.62, "text": " Indirect conversations between"}, {"start": 633.62, "end": 635.62, "text": " Maharaj Yudhishthira and Vidura"}, {"start": 635.62, "end": 637.62, "text": " And thus"}, {"start": 637.62, "end": 639.62, "text": " When she inquired from her son"}, {"start": 639.62, "end": 641.62, "text": " About the purport of the conversation"}, {"start": 641.62, "end": 643.62, "text": " Yudhishthira replied"}, {"start": 643.62, "end": 645.62, "text": " To Kunti Devi"}, {"start": 645.62, "end": 647.62, "text": " That from the talks of Vidura"}, {"start": 647.62, "end": 649.62, "text": " It was understood"}, {"start": 649.62, "end": 651.62, "text": " That there was a hint of fire"}, {"start": 651.62, "end": 653.62, "text": " Proceeding"}, {"start": 653.62, "end": 655.62, "text": " Later"}, {"start": 655.62, "end": 657.62, "text": " On Vidura came"}, {"start": 657.62, "end": 659.62, "text": " In disguise to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 659.62, "end": 661.62, "text": " And informed them"}, {"start": 661.62, "end": 663.62, "text": " That the housekeeper"}, {"start": 663.62, "end": 665.62, "text": " Was going to set fire to the house"}, {"start": 665.62, "end": 667.62, "text": " On the fourteenth night of the waning moon"}, {"start": 667.62, "end": 669.62, "text": " It was an intrigue"}, {"start": 669.62, "end": 671.62, "text": " Of Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 671.62, "end": 673.62, "text": " That the Pandavas might die"}, {"start": 673.62, "end": 675.62, "text": " Altogether with their mother"}, {"start": 675.62, "end": 677.62, "text": " By his warning"}, {"start": 677.62, "end": 679.62, "text": " That is Vidura's warning"}, {"start": 679.62, "end": 681.62, "text": " Pandavas escaped through a tunnel"}, {"start": 681.62, "end": 683.62, "text": " Underneath the earth"}, {"start": 683.62, "end": 685.62, "text": " So that their escape was also unknown"}, {"start": 685.62, "end": 687.62, "text": " To Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 687.62, "end": 689.62, "text": " So much so that"}, {"start": 689.62, "end": 691.62, "text": " After setting the fire"}, {"start": 691.62, "end": 693.62, "text": " The Kauravas were so certain"}, {"start": 693.62, "end": 695.62, "text": " Of the death of the Pandavas"}, {"start": 695.62, "end": 697.62, "text": " That Dhritarashtra performed"}, {"start": 697.62, "end": 699.62, "text": " The last rites of their death"}, {"start": 699.62, "end": 701.62, "text": " With great cheerfulness"}, {"start": 705.62, "end": 707.62, "text": " During the morning period"}, {"start": 707.62, "end": 709.62, "text": " All the members of the palace"}, {"start": 709.62, "end": 711.62, "text": " Became overwhelmed with lamentation"}, {"start": 711.62, "end": 713.62, "text": " But Vidura did not become so"}, {"start": 713.62, "end": 715.62, "text": " Because Vidura had"}, {"start": 715.62, "end": 717.62, "text": " Knowledge that"}, {"start": 717.62, "end": 719.62, "text": " The Pandavas were alive somewhere"}, {"start": 719.62, "end": 721.62, "text": " There are"}, {"start": 721.62, "end": 723.62, "text": " Many such instances of"}, {"start": 723.62, "end": 725.62, "text": " Calamities and in each"}, {"start": 725.62, "end": 727.62, "text": " Of them Vidura gave"}, {"start": 727.62, "end": 729.62, "text": " Protection to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 729.62, "end": 731.62, "text": " On one hand and on the"}, {"start": 731.62, "end": 733.62, "text": " Other he tried to restrain"}, {"start": 733.62, "end": 735.62, "text": " His brother Dhritarashtra"}, {"start": 735.62, "end": 737.62, "text": " From such"}, {"start": 737.62, "end": 739.62, "text": " Intriguing policies"}, {"start": 739.62, "end": 741.62, "text": " See how"}, {"start": 741.62, "end": 743.62, "text": " Vidura played"}, {"start": 743.62, "end": 745.62, "text": " A"}, {"start": 745.62, "end": 747.62, "text": " Fair role"}, {"start": 747.62, "end": 749.62, "text": " In the"}, {"start": 749.62, "end": 751.62, "text": " Palace politics"}, {"start": 751.62, "end": 753.62, "text": " He tried"}, {"start": 753.62, "end": 755.62, "text": " To prevent his brother"}, {"start": 755.62, "end": 757.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra from doing injustice to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 757.62, "end": 759.62, "text": " And he also kept"}, {"start": 759.62, "end": 761.62, "text": " Warning the Pandavas so that"}, {"start": 761.62, "end": 763.62, "text": " Pandavas might not be killed"}, {"start": 763.62, "end": 765.62, "text": " By Dhritarashtra's"}, {"start": 765.62, "end": 767.62, "text": " Intrigues"}, {"start": 767.62, "end": 769.62, "text": " Therefore"}, {"start": 769.62, "end": 771.62, "text": " It is described here that"}, {"start": 771.62, "end": 773.62, "text": " Vidura was"}, {"start": 773.62, "end": 775.62, "text": " Always partial to the Pandavas"}, {"start": 775.62, "end": 777.62, "text": " Just as"}, {"start": 777.62, "end": 779.62, "text": " A bird protects its"}, {"start": 779.62, "end": 781.62, "text": " Eggs by its wing"}, {"start": 781.62, "end": 783.62, "text": " It is natural"}, {"start": 783.62, "end": 785.62, "text": " When a bird lays an egg"}, {"start": 785.62, "end": 787.62, "text": " So that the"}, {"start": 787.62, "end": 789.62, "text": " Egg can eventually"}, {"start": 789.62, "end": 791.62, "text": " Mature and hatch into a young one"}, {"start": 791.62, "end": 793.62, "text": " So before"}, {"start": 793.62, "end": 795.62, "text": " The egg hatches"}, {"start": 795.62, "end": 797.62, "text": " The bird has to protect that egg"}, {"start": 797.62, "end": 799.62, "text": " Against attack by enemies"}, {"start": 799.62, "end": 801.62, "text": " Or by some other"}, {"start": 801.62, "end": 803.62, "text": " Birds which may come and"}, {"start": 803.62, "end": 805.62, "text": " Or some reptiles can come and eat away the egg"}, {"start": 805.62, "end": 807.62, "text": " So the bird has to protect"}, {"start": 807.62, "end": 809.62, "text": " So like that"}, {"start": 809.62, "end": 811.62, "text": " Vidura in order to"}, {"start": 811.62, "end": 813.62, "text": " Protect the Pandavas against"}, {"start": 813.62, "end": 815.62, "text": " Being killed by"}, {"start": 815.62, "end": 817.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra and Duryodhana"}, {"start": 817.62, "end": 819.62, "text": " And the Kauravas"}, {"start": 819.62, "end": 821.62, "text": " He had to protect them"}, {"start": 821.62, "end": 823.62, "text": " Very very"}, {"start": 823.62, "end": 825.62, "text": " Carefully"}, {"start": 825.62, "end": 827.62, "text": " So"}, {"start": 827.62, "end": 829.62, "text": " This was the"}, {"start": 829.62, "end": 831.62, "text": " The"}, {"start": 831.62, "end": 833.62, "text": " Special protection of Vidura"}, {"start": 833.62, "end": 835.62, "text": " And therefore Yudhishthira makes a"}, {"start": 835.62, "end": 837.62, "text": " Reference to this"}, {"start": 837.62, "end": 839.62, "text": " After Yudhishthira returned after the battle of Kurukshetra"}, {"start": 839.62, "end": 841.62, "text": " How because of Vidura's"}, {"start": 841.62, "end": 843.62, "text": " Protection Yudhishthira"}, {"start": 843.62, "end": 845.62, "text": " And his brothers and even Kunti"}, {"start": 845.62, "end": 847.62, "text": " Were actually"}, {"start": 847.62, "end": 849.62, "text": " Protected against"}, {"start": 849.62, "end": 851.62, "text": " Being"}, {"start": 851.62, "end": 853.62, "text": " Completely"}, {"start": 853.62, "end": 855.62, "text": " Killed and eliminated by"}, {"start": 855.62, "end": 857.62, "text": " Dhritarashtra and company"}, {"start": 857.62, "end": 859.62, "text": " So I will stop here"}, {"start": 859.62, "end": 861.62, "text": " Thank you very much"}, {"start": 861.62, "end": 863.62, "text": " Thank you very much"}]}